<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><h4><a href="https://chessolympiad.fide.com"><strong>Official Website</strong></a></h4> <p>Follow the games here: <a href="https://www.chess.com/events/2022-fide-chess-olympiad">Chess.com</a> | <a href="https://chess24.com/en/watch/live-tournaments/olympiad-chennai-2022-open">Chess24</a> | <a href="https://lichess.org/broadcast/44th-chess-olympiad-2022--open/round-1/T1CUcvwV">Lichess</a> | <a href="https://nxt.chessbomb.com/events/2022-fide-chess-olympiad">Chessbomb</a> | <a href="https://chess-results.com/tnr653631.aspx">Chess-Results</a></p> <hr/> <p><strong>CHENNAI</strong> - The countdown has begun for the world’s biggest chess event, the <a href="https://i.imgur.com/zJI6QF4.png">44th International Chess Olympiad</a>, scheduled to take place from July 28 to August 10 at Poonjeri Village in Mahabalipuram, Tamil Nadu. The grand inaugural ceremony featuring the rich culture and tradition of Tamil Nadu will be attended by Prime Minister Narendra Modi, Chief Minister M.K. Stalin, and other special invitees at Nehru Indoor Stadium on July 28.</p> <p>The Olympiad was originally scheduled to take place in Russia but due to the ongoing Russian-Ukraine war, the International Chess Federation (FIDE) started looking for new bidders. India emerged the topper among other countries and won the opportunity to host the high-profile event for the first time. The Union Government provided the hosting rights of the world’s biggest chess event to Tamil Nadu.</p> <p>Over 2,000 participants from 187 countries across the globe are expected to take part in the event, with the notable exceptions of Russia and China. On June 19, PM Modi flagged off the first-ever torch relay for the Chess Olympiad. The torch was aimed to be taken to 75 cities within the country before arriving in Mahabalipuram. The Tamil Nadu Government has also announced a holiday for schools, colleges, and other non-essential government offices in four districts for Thursday, July 28, in view of the opening day of the Olympiad.</p> <hr/> <h4><strong>Top Teams</strong></h4> <table><thead> <tr> <th align="center"><strong>#</strong></th> <th align="left"><strong>FED</strong></th> <th align="left"><strong>Boards 1/3</strong></th> <th align="center"><strong>Rtg.</strong></th> <th align="left"><strong>Boards 2/4</strong></th> <th align="center"><strong>Rtg.</strong></th> </tr> </thead><tbody> <tr> <td align="center">1</td> <td align="left">🇺🇸 USA</td> <td align="left">Fabiano Caruana</td> <td align="center">2783</td> <td align="left">Levon Aronian</td> <td align="center">2775</td> </tr> <tr> <td align="center"></td> <td align="left"></td> <td align="left">Wesley So</td> <td align="center">2773</td> <td align="left">Leinier Domínguez</td> <td align="center">2754</td> </tr> <tr> <td align="center">2</td> <td align="left">🇮🇳 IND</td> <td align="left">Vidit Gujrathi</td> <td align="center">2714</td> <td align="left">Pentala Harikrishna</td> <td align="center">2720</td> </tr> <tr> <td align="center"></td> <td align="left"></td> <td align="left">Arjun Erigaisi</td> <td align="center">2689</td> <td align="left">S.L. Narayanan</td> <td align="center">2659</td> </tr> <tr> <td align="center">3</td> <td align="left">🇳🇴 NOR</td> <td align="left">Magnus Carlsen</td> <td align="center">2864</td> <td align="left">Aryan Tari</td> <td align="center">2672</td> </tr> <tr> <td align="center"></td> <td align="left"></td> <td align="left">Jon-Ludvig Hammer</td> <td align="center">2638</td> <td align="left">Johan Christiansen</td> <td align="center">2593</td> </tr> <tr> <td align="center">4</td> <td align="left">🇪🇸 ESP</td> <td align="left">Alexei Shirov</td> <td align="center">2704</td> <td align="left">Francisco Vallejo</td> <td align="center">2702</td> </tr> <tr> <td align="center"></td> <td align="left"></td> <td align="left">David Antón</td> <td align="center">2667</td> <td align="left">Jaime Santos</td> <td align="center">2675</td> </tr> <tr> <td align="center">5</td> <td 